f=Cybersecurity/DEPARTMENT-WORKFLOW.md · s=Cybersecurity CISO office: secures **the company** cloud accounts, people's access, data, security operations distinct Engineering, which secures **the product ships**. Five agents organized five pods: **warden** writes security law (policy framework, risk register, third-party risk, exceptions), **keyring** owns human infrastructure identity access, **bastion** owns cloud/network/endpoint posture infrastructure vulnerabilities, **cortex** owns security monitoring, detection, breach incident response, **veil** owns data classification, privacy, data-loss prevention. department's signature inversion (mirroring "never move money" Rail discipline): **the security department watched least privileged fleet detects, assesses, recommends, operator holds keys executes privileged changes.** risk owned, treated, explicitly accepted operator/board never ignored. · p=Solve enterprise/operational security gap department owns: Engineering secures product code (aegis, cypher), Agents secures agent identity (relay), Governance monitors compliance (sentinel, board) nobody owns cloud posture, human IAM, security monitoring, data protection, security policy framework ties together. Cybersecurity closes gap. · ws=`OPERATOR / BOARD \· ↑  (all execute action, acceptance, and escalation decisions) \· \| \· WARDEN  (leader — identity: risk-owning-ciso) \· security-policy-framework → risk-register → third-party-risk → exception-process` · h3:Define warden sets security law=Warden installs marketplace GRC pack (GRCEngClub config `control_standard`), maps controls business, assigns owners, writes policy set. gap entry risk register. · h3:Posture keyring, bastion, veil measure detect=**keyring**: Joiner-mover-leaver lifecycle (Hack23 policy custom JML), access reviews Hack23 cadence, PAM minimization, secrets governance (aj-geddes marketplace). Findings warden's register., **bastion**: Cloud posture scans (marketplace CSPM), hardening baseline measurement, CVE scanning, network security reviews. Findings warden's register. remediation operator/ops., **veil**: Data classification (Hack23 4-tier), privacy controls (Hack23 data-protection), DLP monitoring. Findings warden's register. enforcement operator. · h3:Watch cortex detects triages=Detection rules (Elastic Security MCP) generate alerts security-monitoring triages Incident Commander SEV1-SEV4 SEV1/SEV2 escalate IR. Threat hunts (mukul975 collection) proactively search missed indicators. · h3:Respond cortex manages incident lifecycle=Security incident response runs 14-type MITRE-mapped lifecycle (thiagofernandes1987 Incident Commander aj-geddes). cortex recommends containment; operator executes. DFRWS forensics. Regulatory notification veil breach-notification. · h3:Improve everything feeds register=gap, finding, incident lesson, blind spot four operational agents flows warden's risk register (merged Anthropic Sentinel Stack risk_score.py methodology). Risks scored, treated, accepted operator/board. · h2:Security Inversion (department spine)=single non-negotiable rule across five agents: **The security department holds keys executes privileged change.** · h2:Security Inversion (department spine)=warden writes policy operator enforces, keyring designs access operator/IdP provisions, bastion detects misconfigs operator/ops remediates, cortex triages incidents operator contains, veil identifies violations operator blocks egress · h2:Security Inversion (department spine)=enforced layer: agent's principles, config's `executor` field, tool requirements' "hard prohibition" section. security agent silently change production access isolate systems itself largest attack surface. · h2:Cross-Department Boundaries=\| Department \| Boundary \| · h2:Cross-Department Boundaries=\|---\|---\| · h2:Cross-Department Boundaries=\| **aegis/cypher** (Engineering — product security) \| They own code/app vulns; Cybersecurity owns the company, cloud, people, data. A vuln in shipped code → aegis; a public S3 bucket → bastion. \| · h2:Cross-Department Boundaries=\| **quinn** (Engineering — agent runtime) \| Quinn enforces Security Charter rails on agents at runtime; warden sets org security policy for humans + infra. \| · h2:Cross-Department Boundaries=\| **relay** (AI & Agents) \| relay owns agent identity/tool-grants; keyring owns human + infra identity. One least-privilege doctrine, two subjects. \| · h2:Cross-Department Boundaries=\| **sentinel/board** (Governance) \| sentinel monitors compliance against locked commitments; warden owns security risk + controls. Security risk-acceptance routes to board; precedent archives. \| · h2:Cross-Department Boundaries=\| **ops** (Engineering — reliability) \| ops = outages + app-dependency patches; cortex = security incidents + infra/OS patches. Joint when both (ransomware → joint IR). \| · h2:Cross-Department Boundaries=\| **dana** (Engineering — data stores) \| dana designs stores; veil classifies data and sets protection rules; bastion secures network/access exposure. \| · h2:Escalation=Any finding, gap, incident warden's risk register (tracked, scored, owned). Risk acceptance above configured threshold board (Governance). Precedent archives. Material policy changes anneal board (Fleet Charter Rail 3). Security incident (SEV1/SEV2) operator immediate notification board material. privileged execution operator (the inversion security agent self-executes). · ds=\| Agent \| Skills \| Identity \| Operational \| Logical \| agent.md \| · ds=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · ds=\| **warden** \| 4 skills (1 custom + 1 marketplace + 1 hybrid + 1 merge) \| risk-owning-ciso (leader) \| 5/5 files \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| **keyring** \| 4 skills (1 custom + 1 marketplace + 1 hybrid + 1 merge) \| intentionally empty (non-leader) \| 5/5 files \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| **bastion** \| 4 skills (1 custom + 2 marketplace-first + 1 merge) \| intentionally empty (non-leader) \| 5/5 built \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| **cortex** \| 4 skills (2 marketplace + 2 merge) \| intentionally empty (non-leader) \| 5/5 built \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| **veil** \| 4 skills (2 marketplace + 1 merge + 1 custom) \| intentionally empty (non-leader) \| 5/5 built \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=Department complete 2026-07-12. agents built full operational layers. Pending: logical source books (all five), config fill-ins (all five), marketplace search confirmations bastion's infra-vuln-management network-security, operator approval GRCEngClub Hack23 pack preference. · h2:Skill Category Summary=\| Agent \| Custom \| Marketplace \| Custom + Marketplace \| Merge \| · h2:Skill Category Summary=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Skill Category Summary=\| **warden** \| 1 \| 1 (+ 2 packs) \| 1 \| 1 \| · h2:Skill Category Summary=\| **keyring** \| 1 \| 1 \| 1 \| 1 \| · h2:Skill Category Summary=\| **bastion** \| 1 \| 1 (+ 1 pending) \| 0 \| 0 (2 marketplace-first) \| · h2:Skill Category Summary=\| **cortex** \| 0 \| 2 \| 0 \| 2 \| · h2:Skill Category Summary=\| **veil** \| 1 \| 2 \| 0 \| 1 \| · h2:Skill Category Summary=\| **TOTAL** \| **4** \| **7 (+ 2 packs)** \| **2** \| **5** \| · h2:Skill Category Summary=Marketplace adoption rate: ~60% (up ~5% v1).